{
  "texts": [
    "In particular, teacher's professional development and language learning emphasize reflective practice and metacognition (Belvis et al., 2013; Zahid and Khanam, 2019).",
    "For example, research on teachers' noticing highlights the importance of their cognition and behavior in classroom situations (Chan et al., 2021; Amador et al., 2021).",
    "In language learning, metacognitive awareness has been found to enhance foreign language writing ability, emphasizing the need for metacognitive strategies to improve learners' skills (Ramadhanti and Yanda, 2021; Farahian, 2015).",
    "These requirements for introspective behavior and metacognition in language learning and teachers' professional development align with the essential steps and reflective characteristics of SR.",
    "The relationship between stimuli and educational context."
  ]
}